{
  "analysis": "We have no prior output; we're root in /app. The task says running /usr/bin/curl example.com fails. We need to reproduce the failure, identify the cause (DNS, network, proxies, path/symlink issues, CA certs, etc.), and fix it so that /usr/bin/curl example.com succeeds.",
  "plan": "1) Reproduce the issue with verbose output to see exactly why it fails. 2) Check whether /usr/bin/curl is the expected binary (not a broken symlink/wrapper). 3) Check environment proxy variables that may affect curl. 4) Check DNS resolution of example.com and /etc/hosts. 5) If DNS is broken, inspect /etc/resolv.conf and fix it to a working resolver (e.g., 1.1.1.1/8.8.8.8) if appropriate. 6) If TLS/CA is the issue, test http:// vs https:// and install/refresh ca-certificates. 7) If network routing is the issue, test general connectivity with getent/route. 8) After fixing, verify that /usr/bin/curl example.com works.",
